      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "In 1989, Spacone analyzed a software program for voicecontrolled text creation that was used on a microcomputer in the emergency medical department of a large hospital. It was found that automated speech recognition (ASR) permitted doctors to produce their reports faster and more accurately than handwriting or dictation to tape."
